From: BenOS <ben@benos.dev>
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] irqchip: riscv-intc: use 12-bit mask for CLIC mcause

ESP32-P4's CLIC produces mcause with mpp/mpie/mpil in bits 30:16
(e.g., 0xB8000007 for timer interrupt). The existing mask
(~CAUSE_IRQ_FLAG = 0x7FFFFFFF) only clears bit 31, leaving the
CLIC status bits in the cause number. Linux then sees interrupt
0x38000007 instead of 7.

Mask to 12-bit exccode field instead. On non-CLIC hardware, bits
30:12 are always zero, so this change is backwards-compatible.

---
 drivers/irqchip/irq-riscv-intc.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/irqchip/irq-riscv-intc.c
+++ b/drivers/irqchip/irq-riscv-intc.c
@@ -28,7 +28,7 @@
 static asmlinkage void riscv_intc_irq(struct pt_regs *regs)
 {
-	unsigned long cause = regs->cause & ~CAUSE_IRQ_FLAG;
+	unsigned long cause = regs->cause & 0xFFF; /* 12-bit exccode (CLIC-safe) */
 
 	if (unlikely(cause >= RISCV_INTC_NR_IRQS))
 		pr_err("unexpected interrupt cause %#lx", regs->cause);
